block.comment: Set robot variable to ip address or hostname of robot

Initialize all of the variables HALT is used to stop the robot speed is the general speed and right_speed and left_speed are specific to each motor stop_count is used to count how long robot is stopped stopped is used to tell whether the robot is currently stopped
If we aren't already stopped then back up a little and stop. Set stop_count to 1.
Spider isn't too close and we see it (w>0) so calculate the left and right speed based on how far to the left or right spider is and move robot
We don't see the spider and we stopped for less than 2 counts, then back up again to see if we can find it.
We don't see the spider and either we aren't stopped or we stopped and backed up and still couldn't see the spider. Stop, beep twice.
We are lost, turn the robot based on the last x value we had last time we saw the spider
Repeat loop until HALT is true (when space is pressed)

custom-block.comment: We have halted, stop the motors

block.comment: Use space bar to stop the robot

block.l: var sprite = this, stage = sprite.parentThatIsA(StageMorph), context = stage.penTrails().getContext('2d'), isWarped = sprite.isWarped, img = new Image(), left =0, top = 0; if (isWarped) { sprite.endWarp(); } //img.src = 'http://snap.berkeley.edu/half-snapshot.png'; img.src = 'data:image/png;base64,' + image context.save(); context.scale(1 / stage.scale, 1 / stage.scale); context.translate(left, top); context.rotate((sprite.heading - 90) * Math.PI/180); context.drawImage( img, 0, 0 ); context.restore(); stage.changed(); if (isWarped) { sprite.startWarp(); }
